We conducted X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS) to explore the band diagrams of the Ga2O3/MgO/Nb:STO and the Ga2O3/Nb:STO heterostructures (Fig. 2a and Supplementary Fig. S3)30. According to Kraut’s method, the ΔEV could then be determined by analyzing the binding energy difference between the valence band maximum (VBM) and the core-level shifts (see “Methods” section)28. The obtained ΔEV for the Ga2O3/Nb:STO is 0.46 eV, while the ΔEV for the Ga2O3/MgO/Nb:STO is △EV−Ga2O3/MgO\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
